textBeforeTable: Conan's Career Statistics   PERSONAL DATA: Born in Santa Clara, Calif ... parents are Kevin and Sharon Conan ... has two older siblings, Michelle and Sean ... volunteered at the Boys and Girls Club throughout high school ... enjoys fishing, lifting weights and outdoor activities ... major is undeclared ... hopes to become a successful teacher after college. HIGH SCHOOL INFORMATION: A 2004 graduate of Archbishop Mitty High School in San Jose, Calif ... played for Coach Bill Hutton ... team won Central Coast Section Championship in 2003 ... team also advanced to the CCS semi-final game in both 2002 and 2004 ... three-time All-Central Coast Section ... also three-time First Team All-West Catholic Athletic League honoree ... two-time recipient of the team's Coaches Award ... hit .400 in senior season with five home runs and 40 RBI. AS A FRESHMAN IN 2005: Started 14 of the 31 games in which he appeared ... doubled once in three at-bats against UC Riverside on January 30 ... went 1-for-4 with a two-run home run at San Francisco on March 25 ... had his best game of the year on April 26 at Stanford, going 3-for-4 with an RBI AS A SOPHOMORE IN 2006: Appeared in 38 games, starting 16 ... singled an drove in a pair of runs at Pacific on Feb. 5 ... doubled and drove in a run against San Diego State on Feb. 12 ... hit a solo homer against Northwestern on March 19 ... went 2-for-3
